# Git / GitHub Workflow

Use this workflow when the user asks to commit, push, or sync to GitHub.

## Git executable

- **Never install or reinstall Git** for this project.
- Use portable MinGit at `.tools/mingit/cmd/git.exe` (repo root: `C:\Users\user\Documents\Cursor`).
- PowerShell example:

```powershell
$git = Join-Path (Get-Location) ".tools\mingit\cmd\git.exe"
& $git status
```

If `git` is not recognized in the shell, that is normal — always use the path above.

## Remote

- **origin:** `https://github.com/kthngan/Cursor.git`
- **branch:** `main`

## Commit workflow

1. Run in parallel: `git status`, `git diff`, `git log -5 --oneline` (via portable git).
2. Stage only relevant source files — never secrets (`.env`, credentials) or ignored data (`Data/`, `Reports/`, `.tools/`).
3. Commit with a concise message focused on why.
4. Do **not** run `git config`. For identity, set `GIT_AUTHOR_*` / `GIT_COMMITTER_*` env vars if needed.
5. Push: `git push -u origin main` (or `git push` if upstream exists).
6. If push blocks with no output, the user may need to complete GitHub authentication in the browser (Credential Manager).

## Push workflow

```powershell
$git = ".tools\mingit\cmd\git.exe"
& $git add <files>
& $git commit -m "message"
& $git push origin main
```

Only commit when the user explicitly asks.
